# Keep LF in the working tree on every platform. The build runs POSIX shell
# scripts (krudd.sh, krudd/third_party/sync.sh) under MSYS2 on Windows and
# verifies the vendored s7.c/s7.h by sha256 — a CRLF conversion on a Windows
# checkout (autocrlf) would break the shebang lines and change those checksums
# (see krudd/third_party/sync.sh, which would then re-download pristine upstream
# and still mismatch, because s7.c's pin is the checksum of a locally-patched
# file — see krudd/third_party/s7.artifact). Normalizing to LF everywhere keeps
# a Windows checkout byte-identical to Linux and the Deck. No-op on those, which
# are already LF.
* text=auto eol=lf

# The vendored s7 amalgamation: never touch its bytes at all. Its sha256 is
# pinned and s7.c additionally carries a local patch, so it must round-trip a
# checkout unchanged on every platform.
krudd/third_party/s7.c -text
krudd/third_party/s7.h -text

# Binary assets — leave untouched (git's binary detection already spares these,
# but be explicit so no future text rule can reach them).
*.png binary
*.ico binary
